it of international proportions  VMI MuseumChronicles the creation and development of VMI and the amazing contributions of alumni to history  Visit Website   VMI ArchivesThe Virginia Military Institute Archives  located in Preston Library  contain a wealth of 19th and 20th century collections of interest to both scholars and the general public  Visit Website   New Market BattlefieldNew Market Battlefield State Historical Park  19th Century Bushong Farm  and Hall of Valor Civil War Museum  commemorate a unique moment in American history  New Market Battlefield   Center for Leadership and EthicsIn addition to enhancing the experience of current cadets  the Center offers programs in leadership and ethics in a variety of platforms to a broader national audience  Visit Marshall Hall   Marshall MuseumGeneral George C  Marshall s life and leadership during war and peace exemplified the values of selfless service  dedicated effort  and strength of character  Marshall Museum   Stonewall Jackson HouseA museum showcasing Thomas J   Stonewall  Jackson s former home and its collections  Jackson House Website   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 